@predatell safe engineering practices dictate ranges of versions that are inclusive of their bounds, and have undergone full unit + integration testing with the software artifact.

Your suggestion of `lxml >= 4.0.0` is negligent and dangerous.  What if `5.0.0` introduces breaking API changes?  What if `4.1.0` introduces a **backdoor** into the codebase to steal CC info?  Or even just a plain remote code execution CVE?  We wouldn't want users blindly using that with this project!

It is much safer to use a precise range of versions that has been tested with.

