@bjf thank you for reporting this. In this case, we're returning the error message that service serves us. Though the output does contain sufficient information for the users to correct the input, the form of the output is not ideal. However, as @tjprescott pointed out you can change the output format to make the error message more readable by setting the output format. I hope it works for you.

Moving forward, it worth to revisit how we output the returned value when the service indicates the operation is failed. However, this will be larger task impacts the entire output and formatting model. And we do need to consider this topic from many different perspectives besides error messages.

Thank you for the reporting. I will close this issue for now.

