@pjbreaux : Only reset-stats are supported as it globally resets the stats for the object.

We can drop .value so calling the vs.stats.clientside_curConns. would return a dictionary for example:
{'value':'100'}

The problem i see is that this will be awkward from user's perspective and i think its much more elegant to access value as a property, the same way we access property for say: VirtualServer.

It is important to note that all of the values are Read only, and only way to modify them is to use reset-stats command which will basically reset them to zero or none.

