@cancan101 I think your solution is fine. Marshmallow will not have first-class support for SQLalchemy (or any other ORM).

That said, if we decide to implement something like the `add_fields` option discussed in https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/issues/139#issuecomment-73638482 , you would be able to generate fields from a Model, like so:

```python
from marshmallow import Schema

# function adapted from lima docs: https://lima.readthedocs.org/en/latest/advanced.html
def fields_for_model(model):
    result = {}
    for name, col in model.__mapper__.columns.items():
        field_class = Schema.TYPE_MAPPING[col.type.python_type]
        result[name] = field_class()
    return result

class MySchema(Schema):
    class Meta:
        add_fields = fields_for_model(MyModel)
```

